427
00:21:29,161 --> 00:21:32,061
What's this crazy diamond about?

428
00:21:32,061 --> 00:21:33,561
What is it, anyway?

429
00:21:33,561 --> 00:21:37,261
So, it's a type of optical illusion, you see.

430
00:21:37,261 --> 00:21:40,061
Kazuha's cell phone is ringing!

431
00:21:42,761 --> 00:21:44,361
Hello?

432
00:21:44,361 --> 00:21:47,461
Hey, detective boy from Osaka.

433
00:21:47,461 --> 00:21:50,061
That voice! You're Inspector Yamato, aren't you?

434
00:21:50,061 --> 00:21:54,861
We just found the dying message of the president in question!

435
00:21:54,861 --> 00:21:56,361
Really?

436
00:21:56,361 --> 00:22:01,361
Three letters of the alphabet were written, "S-O-N"!

437
00:22:01,361 --> 00:22:04,561
Huh? "S-O-N"?

438
00:22:04,561 --> 00:22:06,461
S-O-N...

439
00:22:06,461 --> 00:22:07,661
Son.

440
00:22:07,661 --> 00:22:08,961
His son?

441
00:22:08,961 --> 00:22:11,061
Yeah! If the killer of the case over here,

442
00:22:11,061 --> 00:22:13,861
and over there are the same,

443
00:22:13,861 --> 00:22:15,761
nab his son!

444
00:22:15,761 --> 00:22:18,861
Then, this case is closed!

445
00:22:18,861 --> 00:22:21,861
-That's impossible. -What?

446
00:22:21,861 --> 00:22:24,861
The one who was murdered here tonight

447
00:22:24,861 --> 00:22:26,961
is that son, that's why.

448
00:22:26,961 --> 00:22:29,361
What?

449
00:22:29,361 --> 00:22:32,761
In other words, the one who murdered the president

450
00:22:32,761 --> 00:22:36,361
